FBIS3-17806 "drsov061_a_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Shokhin, Dubinin Meet Brown Delegation LD2903213894 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 1943 GMT 29 Mar 94 LD2903213894 Moscow 2x2 Television Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] In the Radisson Slavyanskaya hotel a round table took place at which members of the American delegation headed by U.S. Secretary of Commerce Ronald Brown and representatives of the Russian Government met. The signing of an agreement on civil peace will be the main condition for economic and political stabilization in the country, Deputy Prime Minister Aleksandr Shokhin stated at the meeting. Sergey Dubinin gave the American businessmen the assurance that Russia's financial stabilization is becoming a reality: He believes that by the end of the year inflation will not exceed 5-7 percent per month.
